descript.abstract: Places represents all places within the province. Includes cities, towns, villages, and deserted areas, among others.
descript.purpose: The Provincial Cartographic Base Layers are essentially the digital equivalent of the information contained in a road map. These layers can be used to show the location of places and geographic features, and help students learn about the general geography of the provinces and territories.
descript.supplinf: The Provincial Level Dataset, at a scale of 1:1 Million, contains many useful cartographic and thematic layers.
